However, this individual is one of the ones I took notes on should I ever be faced with the unpleasant prospect of dealing with him again.<br>
<br>
I was in the bazaar one night shopping for spells when I noticed Sidburn asking in ooc for a rez.  At first I though the bazaar was a strange place to be asking for a rez, but I figure stranger things can and do happen.  Anyway I get a tell from him asking if I would be willing to rez him at the spires in Gfay for a donation.  I first do a /who all sidburn to find he is a level low 50ish and unguilded ( to the best of my recollection ).  So I respond saying I would be willing to, but it will take me about 10 minutes to finish my business here if you would like to wait.  He agrees.<br>
<br>
After about 10 minutes I still was not done, and he is starts asking in ooc for a rez again.  No problem, if he can get one, I can go ahead and log, since its late for me anyway.  I complete my transactions and its about 20 minutes from his first tell, so I send him a tell asking if he still needs a rez.  He says yes, so I’m on my way.  While traveling there he says he died because of a stupid mistake.  Oh well, no biggie, I find his corpse, ask him if he is ready, and give him a 96pct rez.<br>
<br>
As soon as he pops, I heal him, he turns a little towards me, then back, sits and throws his AFK flag on.  I’m thinking WTF?  That’s kind of rude IMO.  I wait about two minutes, then decide he isn’t worth my time or effort, so I send him a tell something like “Thanks for your courtesy and donation” and left.  He never replied or said anything else.<br>
<br>
I’m happy he has found a home here on MT’s most hated.  I’ll vote for him to stay here.<br>
I know I will not choose to deal with him again.<br>
<br>
Ninlaana Nitestorm<br>
58 Cleric<br>
